wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval: Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request parameter is invalid.
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-unsup:
Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request parameter specifies an unsupported version.

Parameters:
* $1 – the supported versions (comma-separated list)
* $2 – the number of supported versions
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval:
Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request parameter contains no valid field to specify the property ID to reconcile on.

Parameters:
* $1 – the version of the request parameter, e.g. 0.0.1
* $2 – the name of the field, e.g. urlReconcile
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-prope: Error returned when a property was not found by its label
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval:
Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request propertyId parameter is not of type URL.

Parameters:
* $1 – the name of the property, e.g. P123
* $2 – the name of the field, e.g. urlReconcile.
* $3 – the datatype of the provided reconcile property, e.g. string
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-unspe: Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter contains no version field in the entity input
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval:
Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter specifies an unsupported version.

Parameters:
* $1 is the specified (unsupported) version, $2 the supported versions, and $3 the number of supported versions
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-quali: Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter specifies qualifiers and/or references. They are not yet supported.
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-recon: Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter doesn't contain a statement that uses the reconciliation property
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval: Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter if the reconciliation statement's mainsnak is not of type value
Error returned by the API if the JSON request body is invalid or empty.

Error returned by the API if the request content type is invalid.

Parameters:
* $1 – the expected content type
wikibasereconcileedit-reconciliationserv:
Error returned by the API if the reconciliation request matches multiple items.

Parameters:
* $1 – the matched items (comma-separated list)
* $2 – the number of matched items
wikibasereconcileedit-minimaliteminput-r:
Error returned by the API if the minimal item input statements parameter is missing a certain key.

Parameters:
 $1 - the missing key
wikibasereconcileedit-fullwikibaseitemin:
Error returned by the API if the full wikibase item input's type parameter is not supported.

Parameters:
* $1 – the supported types (comma-separated list)
* $2 – the number of supported types
wikibasereconcileedit-unauthorized-acces: Error returned by the API if not authorized access
